snippet.textDisplay:
Top o' the mornin'!

I'm Irish - Irish the Hedgehog!

I was going to meet up with me old friends Tilly and Sonk, when suddenly I thought; "You know, I've a mouth on me for some good ol' parties..."

And so the I went down to Station Square and I bump into Big and it's just like; "How's the Big size a ye?" and he's all like; "Irish! How in the name of Tikal are ye?"

And I'm just all "Story horse, how's it going, ah sure grand." and then he's like "Sonk was just here, but that eijit was natterin' about nothin."

And so then I thought of me old fella, and suddenly Big says "Get outta that garden!" and I thought be might've gone stone mad and maybe he's just sick as a box o' frogs.

But then I'm thinking we'll with Big, he's a few short of a full shilling now, y'know what I'm saying? and quite frankly his mouth is the size of a old out skip and some say he's the owner o' the Giant's Causeway.

And so I finally meet up with Tilly and he's stressin' and he's all in n' out like a fiddler's elbow and o' Tilly's one o' the lads y'know?
